1
00:00:09,958 --> 00:00:11,583
[SHATTERING SOUND]

2
00:00:15,291 --> 00:00:18,250
Who are you? Speak.

3
00:02:10,916 --> 00:02:12,541
[FRIENDER WHIMPERS]

4
00:02:12,625 --> 00:02:14,583
[FRIENDER GROWLS]

5
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:20,916
[FRIENDER GROWLS]

6
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:23,958
I didn't... mean to.

7
00:02:35,791 --> 00:02:40,750
[CASSHERN GRUNTS]

8
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:50,958
[CASSHERN YELLS]

9
00:02:53,916 --> 00:02:58,875
[AKOES BREATHES HEAVILY]

10
00:03:01,541 --> 00:03:03,000
Heh...

11
00:03:05,083 --> 00:03:09,208
[AKOES BREATHES HEAVILY]

12
00:03:12,916 --> 00:03:15,791
Heh... Ahh... Blockheads.

13
00:03:15,875 --> 00:03:17,125
[AKOES SIGHS]

14
00:03:18,583 --> 00:03:26,708
[AKOES COUGHS]

15
00:03:33,833 --> 00:03:43,625
[METALLIC CLATTERING
AND CRUMBLING SOUNDS]

16
00:03:43,708 --> 00:03:45,875
[CASSHERN WHIMPERS]

17
00:04:00,458 --> 00:04:04,125
[FOOTSTEPS]

18
00:04:06,166 --> 00:04:09,125
[FRIENDER GROWLS]

19
00:04:11,208 --> 00:04:15,583
[FRIENDER GROWLS]

20
00:04:15,666 --> 00:04:18,000
I'm leaving now.

21
00:04:18,083 --> 00:04:21,541
So what are you going to do?

22
00:04:36,625 --> 00:04:39,791
[AKOES WHEEZES]

23
00:04:39,875 --> 00:04:43,416
[AKOES INHALES DEEPLY]

24
00:04:45,458 --> 00:04:48,333
[AKOES SIGHS]

25
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:53,916
Huh...?

26
00:05:02,375 --> 00:05:05,500
[AKOES WHISTLES]

27
00:05:13,916 --> 00:05:16,083
[AKOES] Hey!

28
00:05:17,458 --> 00:05:20,583
Your quite a rarity
around here. Heh...

29
00:05:20,666 --> 00:05:22,916
Don't see to many bodies
like yours anymore...

30
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:26,625
Completely unaffected
by the ruin...

31
00:05:26,708 --> 00:05:31,291
Don't get involved
with me... or you'll die.

32
00:05:31,375 --> 00:05:33,416
What, no hello?

33
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:36,666
[AKOES] You think you're
the grim reaper or something?

34
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:39,333
[AKOES STAMMERS]

35
00:05:39,416 --> 00:05:41,291
Hey wait! Hold on!

36
00:05:41,375 --> 00:05:45,083
I was just taken aback when
you said I'd die, that's all!

37
00:05:45,166 --> 00:05:47,375
Grim reaper
just slipped out...

38
00:05:47,458 --> 00:05:50,333
Didn't mean
to offend...

39
00:05:50,416 --> 00:05:52,333
Are you hearing me?

40
00:05:52,416 --> 00:05:56,083
I'm just trying to keep the
lines of communication open.

41
00:05:56,166 --> 00:05:57,458
So where're
you going?

42
00:05:57,541 --> 00:06:00,666
Got some business
around here?

43
00:06:00,750 --> 00:06:03,958
I told you... Back off.

44
00:06:07,291 --> 00:06:09,250
[AKOES] Fine...

45
00:06:09,333 --> 00:06:13,083
But let me say
this one last thing!

46
00:06:13,166 --> 00:06:14,916
I've been hearing there's
a community around here 

47
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:18,958
filled with robots who have
accepted the idea of dying.

48
00:06:19,041 --> 00:06:21,958
You got any idea where it is?

49
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:27,666
[CASSHERN]
It doesn't exist anymore.

50
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:30,208
Huh...? What's that?

51
00:06:30,291 --> 00:06:32,833
[CASSHERN GRUNTS]

52
00:06:32,916 --> 00:06:35,833
I said they're not there!

53
00:06:40,125 --> 00:06:42,958
Hmm...

54
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,375
[AKOES GRUNTS]

55
00:06:49,375 --> 00:06:50,916
[AKOES LAUGHS]

56
00:06:52,333 --> 00:07:02,291
[AKOES WHISTLES]

57
00:07:02,375 --> 00:07:11,375
[AKOES WHISTLES]

58
00:07:11,458 --> 00:07:12,208
[AKOES LAUGHS]

59
00:07:12,291 --> 00:07:14,666
Is my whistling too loud?

60
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:16,583
I told you to keep
your distance.

61
00:07:16,666 --> 00:07:18,208
Yeah, I know...

62
00:07:18,291 --> 00:07:20,916
But I'm here so
what can you do?

63
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,708
Besides, you seem
like an interesting guy.

64
00:07:23,791 --> 00:07:26,375
Woah, don't glare
at me like that man!

65
00:07:26,458 --> 00:07:29,791
It's not like I'm
gonna try to eat you.

66
00:07:30,916 --> 00:07:34,041
With a look like that I'd say
you're about to eat me!

67
00:07:34,125 --> 00:07:36,791
So earlier you said if
I got involved with you

68
00:07:36,875 --> 00:07:38,291
I would die...

69
00:07:38,375 --> 00:07:40,666
Are you planning on killing me?

70
00:07:40,750 --> 00:07:41,958
[CASSHERN]
What if I was?

71
00:07:42,041 --> 00:07:43,500
[AKOES] Ohh...

72
00:07:43,583 --> 00:07:46,666
Wouldn't matter to me since
I was killed a long time ago.

73
00:07:50,041 --> 00:07:52,625
Hey relax pal... see I
know just what it takes

74
00:07:52,708 --> 00:07:55,750
to walk side-by-side
with the grim reaper.

75
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:58,166
[CASSHERN GASPS]

76
00:07:58,250 --> 00:08:01,166
[AKOES]
Come on. Let's keep moving.

77
00:08:07,041 --> 00:08:08,666
[AKOES] Hey!

78
00:08:08,750 --> 00:08:12,000
Slow down will ya?
You're too damn fast!

79
00:08:12,083 --> 00:08:13,750
How 'bout a little
consideration?

80
00:08:13,833 --> 00:08:17,500
My legs don't work
as good as yours!

81
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:22,833
[AKOES] What are you in
such a hurry for anyway?

82
00:08:22,916 --> 00:08:25,375
Let's rest a minute...

83
00:08:25,458 --> 00:08:27,791
Trust me, there's nowhere
worth hurrying to

84
00:08:27,875 --> 00:08:30,666
in this wasteland of a planet.

85
00:08:33,250 --> 00:08:34,583
Come on...

86
00:08:34,666 --> 00:08:37,000
You know it's true.

87
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,666
I say we take our time...

88
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:42,583
I mean... I'm sure you
have your reasons

89
00:08:42,666 --> 00:08:45,541
for wanting to speeding ahead.

90
00:08:45,625 --> 00:08:48,666
Well I've got
some of my own.

91
00:08:48,750 --> 00:08:52,541
[AKOES GULPS]

92
00:08:52,625 --> 00:08:55,166
[AKOES EXHALES HEAVILY]

93
00:08:56,666 --> 00:08:58,500
You wanna
take a swig?

94
00:08:58,583 --> 00:09:02,333
Though I'm not sure it'll
quench your robotic taste buds.

95
00:09:03,291 --> 00:09:04,916
A Human?

96
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,291
Heh...

97
00:09:06,375 --> 00:09:09,250
Ha! Is this the first
time you've seen one of us?

98
00:09:09,333 --> 00:09:11,583
Seems like our numbers
are dwindling nowadays.

99
00:09:11,666 --> 00:09:14,041
But we're not as rare
as you might think.

100
00:09:14,125 --> 00:09:15,458
Huh?

101
00:09:15,541 --> 00:09:16,958
What?

102
00:09:17,041 --> 00:09:18,125
Nothing.

103
00:09:18,208 --> 00:09:19,458
Heh...

104
00:09:19,541 --> 00:09:21,333
Seems to me like someone's
starting to get curious

105
00:09:21,416 --> 00:09:23,958
about the talkative human.

106
00:09:27,916 --> 00:09:29,916
[AKOES GRUNTS]

107
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,375
Hmph...

108
00:09:35,416 --> 00:09:38,125
[AKOES] You know, being human's
not all it's cracked up to be.

109
00:09:38,208 --> 00:09:40,000
If we don't eat we starve,

110
00:09:40,083 --> 00:09:42,291
and if we do eat
we have to shit.

111
00:09:42,375 --> 00:09:44,958
And if we don't have water,
that alone will kill us.

112
00:09:45,041 --> 00:09:46,500
Kinda sucks...

113
00:09:46,583 --> 00:09:48,708
For our entire lives
we're bound by

114
00:09:48,791 --> 00:09:51,166
the limitations of our bodies.

115
00:09:51,250 --> 00:09:55,000
We can't just replace
parts like you can.

116
00:09:56,875 --> 00:10:00,375
[AKOES SIPS]

117
00:10:00,458 --> 00:10:03,958
[AKOES] As far as life-forms go,
we're pretty inefficient...

118
00:10:04,041 --> 00:10:07,125
But now at least we're
on the same level as robots.

119
00:10:07,208 --> 00:10:09,625
You can thank
the ruin for that.

120
00:10:11,541 --> 00:10:13,708
The ruin...

121
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,791
[AKOES] Companionship for
travels and kindness for life.

122
00:10:17,875 --> 00:10:21,125
Our time together may not
be very long, but nonetheless,

123
00:10:21,208 --> 00:10:24,208
it's nice to meet you,
Mister Whoever-you-are.

124
00:10:24,291 --> 00:10:26,833
Uh, well...
I'm... Casshern.

125
00:10:26,916 --> 00:10:28,916
And I'm Akoes.

126
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:31,833
Hmm... Casshern...?

127
00:10:31,916 --> 00:10:34,083
Casshern...

128
00:10:35,666 --> 00:10:39,208
Nice to meet
you... Casshern.

129
00:10:39,291 --> 00:10:41,333
Yeah.

130
00:10:42,708 --> 00:10:44,541
[AKOES GRUNTS]

131
00:10:53,875 --> 00:10:55,375
[CRUMBLING SOUND]

132
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:12,416
[CLATTERING]

133
00:11:18,458 --> 00:11:21,500
[SCRAPING]

134
00:11:21,583 --> 00:11:24,750
It's pretty neat, huh?

135
00:11:24,833 --> 00:11:26,500
[CASSHERN]
What is that?

136
00:11:26,583 --> 00:11:29,416
[AKOES] Remember me telling you
how inefficient humans are?

137
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:32,458
We must kill in order to live.

138
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,875
And he's gonna be dead soon.

139
00:11:35,958 --> 00:11:37,083
[CASSHERN GASPS]

140
00:11:37,166 --> 00:11:38,166
He?

141
00:11:38,250 --> 00:11:40,750
[BUMPHEAD LIZARD SQUEAKS]

142
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:42,333
[AKOES YELLS]

143
00:11:43,958 --> 00:11:44,875
Huh?!

144
00:11:46,958 --> 00:11:48,750
Damn...

145
00:11:51,541 --> 00:11:53,333
[CASSHERN]
Akoes.

146
00:11:53,416 --> 00:11:54,833
[AKOES]
I'm starving.

147
00:11:54,916 --> 00:11:57,250
Were you gonna
eat that lizard?

148
00:11:57,333 --> 00:11:59,375
[AKOES COUGHS]

149
00:11:59,458 --> 00:12:02,000
[AKOES INHALES]

150
00:12:03,666 --> 00:12:05,708
I never thought of
eating them before...

151
00:12:05,791 --> 00:12:07,083
But nowadays they're
an important source

152
00:12:07,166 --> 00:12:08,958
of protein for me.

153
00:12:09,041 --> 00:12:10,791
And you'll die
if you don't eat?

154
00:12:10,875 --> 00:12:13,083
Well yeah!

155
00:12:13,166 --> 00:12:16,291
[CASSHERN] So I just need
to catch that little thing?

156
00:12:16,375 --> 00:12:17,208
[AKOES GASPS]

157
00:12:17,291 --> 00:12:20,666
[WHOOSH]

158
00:12:20,750 --> 00:12:23,583
[CRASHING SOUND]

159
00:12:29,291 --> 00:12:31,583
[AKOES LAUGHS]

160
00:12:31,666 --> 00:12:34,125
[AKOES]
Wow... Well done.

161
00:12:36,166 --> 00:12:37,166
[AKOES CHEWS]

162
00:12:37,250 --> 00:12:39,166
[AKOES]
I sympathize with you robots.

163
00:12:39,250 --> 00:12:41,416
I mean, you don't
get to eat or drink,

164
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:43,041
and more than anything
don't get to enjoy

165
00:12:43,125 --> 00:12:44,208
the pleasures of a woman.

166
00:12:44,291 --> 00:12:46,291
I can't imagine that.

167
00:12:47,916 --> 00:12:49,041
[CASSHERN] But weren't
you just talking about

168
00:12:49,125 --> 00:12:52,833
how inefficient
the human body is?

169
00:12:52,916 --> 00:12:54,000
[AKOES LAUGHS]

170
00:12:54,083 --> 00:12:55,875
[AKOES]
All humans are flawed.

171
00:12:55,958 --> 00:12:58,708
We contradict ourselves
with every step we take.

172
00:12:58,791 --> 00:13:01,875
So... we might as well
enjoy the benefits.

173
00:13:04,708 --> 00:13:08,416
That was... damn good.

174
00:13:15,625 --> 00:13:17,375
[FRIENDER WHIMPERS]

175
00:13:23,791 --> 00:13:28,625
[WRENCH] Friender... 
Go... and live your life.

176
00:13:34,333 --> 00:13:37,125
[CRUMBLING]

177
00:13:37,208 --> 00:13:43,083
[FRIENDER HOWLS]

178
00:13:49,458 --> 00:13:53,291
[AKOES] Do you have fun
brooding all the time?

179
00:13:53,375 --> 00:13:55,500
What's done is done man.

180
00:13:55,583 --> 00:13:57,458
Worrying about it
won't change anything,

181
00:13:57,541 --> 00:13:59,958
besides making
you feel worse.

182
00:14:00,041 --> 00:14:02,125
I'm guilty of
committing a sin.

183
00:14:02,208 --> 00:14:05,625
Hey, me too!

184
00:14:05,708 --> 00:14:08,041
But, so what?

185
00:14:11,708 --> 00:14:14,666
[AKOES] Anyone or anything
can make a mistake.

186
00:14:14,750 --> 00:14:18,791
If you mope about it, will
that make the sin disappear?

187
00:14:18,875 --> 00:14:20,541
It's different now.

188
00:14:20,625 --> 00:14:22,541
In fact, it's better
since the world doesn't have

189
00:14:22,625 --> 00:14:24,250
laws to follow.

190
00:14:24,333 --> 00:14:26,458
No laws mean
no punishment.

191
00:14:26,541 --> 00:14:28,833
So you'll be
fine... pal.

192
00:14:28,916 --> 00:14:30,250
Heh... There's
just no sense

193
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:33,625
in brooding over
anything in this world.

194
00:14:33,708 --> 00:14:35,250
I don't get it.

195
00:14:35,333 --> 00:14:36,541
By simply existing

196
00:14:36,625 --> 00:14:40,291
I create nothing but
destruction and disaster.

197
00:14:40,375 --> 00:14:44,958
Everyone who comes
near me ends up dead.

198
00:14:45,041 --> 00:14:48,666
What am I... a monster
or something worse?

199
00:14:50,250 --> 00:14:52,208
How the hell
should I know?

200
00:14:52,291 --> 00:14:55,541
All I do is eat,
shit, and sleep.

201
00:15:01,458 --> 00:15:03,083
[AKOES]
What do you think?

202
00:15:03,166 --> 00:15:04,791
[CASSHERN]
About the mountains?

203
00:15:04,875 --> 00:15:07,125
[AKOES]
Yeah, that's right.

204
00:15:07,208 --> 00:15:10,000
[CASSHERN]
It's just a mountain.

205
00:15:10,083 --> 00:15:11,833
[AKOES] A long time ago,
there were people who would

206
00:15:11,916 --> 00:15:14,166
risk their lives just to
climb to the top of 'em.

207
00:15:14,250 --> 00:15:17,041
They did it for
sport. Crazy huh?

208
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,291
[CASSHERN] Akoes...

209
00:15:22,375 --> 00:15:25,083
Why did you want to
find the commune?

210
00:15:26,750 --> 00:15:29,625
To see... their faces.

211
00:15:32,041 --> 00:15:34,416
[AKOES] I just wanted to
witness with my own two eyes

212
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:39,791
a robot that accepts
the realities of death.

213
00:15:39,875 --> 00:15:42,875
I've been on the run
for most of my life.

214
00:15:42,958 --> 00:15:46,000
I've made a career out of petty
crimes ever since I was a kid,

215
00:15:46,083 --> 00:15:48,583
so it didn't take me
long to find solace

216
00:15:48,666 --> 00:15:50,166
in running away
from my problems

217
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:53,375
rather than facing the
consequences of my actions.

218
00:15:53,458 --> 00:15:56,791
For awhile I blamed myself,
much like you're doing now,

219
00:15:56,875 --> 00:16:01,708
but I soon found that ignoring
them worked out the best.

220
00:16:01,791 --> 00:16:04,666
[AKOES COUGHS]

221
00:16:04,750 --> 00:16:05,791
[AKOES SIGHS]

222
00:16:05,875 --> 00:16:07,708
[CASSHERN] Akoes...?

223
00:16:08,916 --> 00:16:10,791
[AKOES] I'm fine.

224
00:16:12,916 --> 00:16:15,666
Civilization that they believed
would last forever... 

225
00:16:15,750 --> 00:16:18,625
...just disappeared
thanks to the ruin.

226
00:16:18,708 --> 00:16:20,666
All those who took
advantage of this world

227
00:16:20,750 --> 00:16:23,000
died out a long,
long time ago...

228
00:16:23,083 --> 00:16:24,750
And those who had
power were taken out

229
00:16:24,833 --> 00:16:27,500
by those who had more power.

230
00:16:29,125 --> 00:16:32,041
[AKOES] Where am I supposed
to end up in all this?

231
00:16:32,125 --> 00:16:35,541
All I've ever done in
my life is run away.

232
00:16:35,625 --> 00:16:37,416
I mean, where
has it gotten me?

233
00:16:37,500 --> 00:16:40,083
And for what?
To live longer...?

234
00:16:40,166 --> 00:16:43,750
Why am I even alive in
the first place? To run...?

235
00:16:43,833 --> 00:16:47,958
When you get down to the core,
what in the hell am I?

236
00:16:48,041 --> 00:16:51,166
No one seems to
understand that.

237
00:16:55,083 --> 00:16:56,458
[AKOES GRUNTS]

238
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:02,250
So Casshern...

239
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:06,416
Even a dumbass human
like me knows one thing.

240
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:08,416
That being on the run...

241
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:11,125
...isn't anyway to live.

242
00:17:22,958 --> 00:17:25,458
[AKOES COUGHS]

243
00:17:34,541 --> 00:17:36,041
[CASSHERN] Friender...

244
00:17:36,125 --> 00:17:39,666
I've come to make things
right between us.

245
00:17:46,333 --> 00:17:47,708
[FRIENDER GROWLS]

246
00:17:47,791 --> 00:17:49,166
[METALLIC CLANG]

247
00:17:49,250 --> 00:17:52,291
I haven't stopped
thinking about it. But I... 

248
00:17:52,375 --> 00:17:53,416
[FRIENDER GROWLS]

249
00:17:57,833 --> 00:18:02,083
I can't figure out what
the right thing to do is.

250
00:18:02,166 --> 00:18:03,166
Casshern!

251
00:18:03,250 --> 00:18:05,166
[CASSHERN]
Stay away, Akoes!

252
00:18:05,250 --> 00:18:06,750
What the hell is that mutt?!

253
00:18:06,833 --> 00:18:08,291
[FRIENDER GROWLS]

254
00:18:08,375 --> 00:18:11,458
[CASSHERN YELLS]

255
00:18:18,125 --> 00:18:19,541
[CASSHERN]
It's alright...

256
00:18:19,625 --> 00:18:23,583
I made this decision
and I'm sticking to it.

257
00:18:26,666 --> 00:18:30,291
Casshern... you're...

258
00:18:30,375 --> 00:18:33,125
[FRIENDER SNARLS]

259
00:18:36,125 --> 00:18:39,625
[CASSHERN] It's not worth
it... to run... right?

260
00:18:39,708 --> 00:18:41,625
[AKOES GASPS]

261
00:18:41,708 --> 00:18:45,500
[CASSHERN THINKING]
That's why... I've chosen...

262
00:18:45,583 --> 00:18:48,708
...to hand over
my life to Friender.

263
00:18:48,791 --> 00:18:49,666
[AKOES] Casshern!

264
00:18:56,708 --> 00:19:01,416
But Friender...! Why'd you...

265
00:19:03,208 --> 00:19:07,458
[FOOTSTEPS]

266
00:19:11,750 --> 00:19:12,791
[AKOES LAUGHS]

267
00:19:12,875 --> 00:19:15,833
[AKOES] Get out,
you're name's Friender?

268
00:19:15,916 --> 00:19:17,291
How about that?

269
00:19:17,375 --> 00:19:19,958
Yeah, you're a good boy...

270
00:19:20,041 --> 00:19:21,166
Smart too.

271
00:19:21,250 --> 00:19:23,208
[AKOES LAUGHS]

272
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:29,708
[CASSHERN] Akoes...
Friender... Let's go.

273
00:19:36,958 --> 00:19:38,583
Huh...?

274
00:19:38,666 --> 00:19:40,166
Akoes?

275
00:19:40,250 --> 00:19:44,708
Casshern...
This is as far as I go.

276
00:19:44,791 --> 00:19:48,458
I'm gonna head over
to that robot commune.

277
00:19:48,541 --> 00:19:50,666
But wait!
They're not there any--

278
00:19:50,750 --> 00:19:55,000
[AKOES] I know... You
don't have to say anything.

279
00:19:58,416 --> 00:20:00,583
[AKOES] Casshern!

280
00:20:00,666 --> 00:20:03,208
Guess you aren't
the grim reaper after all... 

281
00:20:03,291 --> 00:20:06,708
Just look at me... 
I'm still alive, aren't I?

282
00:20:06,791 --> 00:20:08,625
See ya!

283
00:20:16,541 --> 00:20:18,583
[CASSHERN]
Come on, Friender.

284
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:38,333
[LOUD THUD]

285
00:20:41,416 --> 00:20:44,833
[FRIENDER WHIMPERS]

286
00:20:44,916 --> 00:20:48,708
[AKOES THINKING]
So... this is how it ends.

287
00:20:48,791 --> 00:20:53,208
I was already
half-dead to begin with.

288
00:20:53,291 --> 00:20:55,208
It's strange...

289
00:20:55,291 --> 00:20:57,958
I spent all this
time running alone,

290
00:20:58,041 --> 00:21:02,583
and yet in the end I ended up
palling around with you.

291
00:21:02,666 --> 00:21:04,916
Casshern...

292
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:08,083
Maybe this is what
I wanted all along...

293
00:21:08,166 --> 00:21:12,291
The chance to tell
someone the truth.

294
00:21:12,375 --> 00:21:16,000
I was just looking
for a place to die...

295
00:21:16,083 --> 00:21:18,333
I've committed more
crimes in my life

296
00:21:18,416 --> 00:21:21,250
than I'd like to admit...

297
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:24,583
But I never had
the guts to die alone.

298
00:21:24,666 --> 00:21:26,416
Weird, isn't it?

299
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:30,875
Having the guts to do
something as simple as dying?

300
00:21:30,958 --> 00:21:33,500
Don't worry Casshern...

301
00:21:33,583 --> 00:21:39,000
Life is full of things
you'll never understand.

302
00:22:02,208 --> 00:22:07,166
♪ closing song ♪

303
00:23:33,916 --> 00:23:36,708
[CASSHERN] There was a girl
who found joy in fighting...

304
00:23:36,791 --> 00:23:41,250
...as a way of
sharing her feelings.

305
00:23:41,333 --> 00:23:45,125
Next time...
The Angel of Ruin.

